          "prompt_html": "<h1>MULTIPLE CHOICE 43</h1><p><strong>Questions 11 - 14</strong></p><p>Choose the correct letter, <strong>A, B or C</strong>.</p><p><strong>Westley University Sports Hall - Talk and Tour</strong></p><p>11 Which activity can visitors to the sports centre currently take part in?</p><table><thead><tr><th><strong>A</strong>    Trampolining</th><th></th></tr></thead><tbody><tr><td><strong>B</strong>    Aerobics</td><td></td></tr><tr><td><strong>C</strong>    Yoga</td><td></td></tr></tbody></table><p>12 What can be found in the fitness room?</p><table><thead><tr><th><strong>A</strong>    Weight-training machines</th><th></th></tr></thead><tbody><tr><td><strong>B</strong>    Running machines</td><td></td></tr><tr><td><strong>C</strong>    Exercise mats and balls</td><td></td></tr></tbody></table><p>13 What could result in being banned from the sports centre?</p><table><thead><tr><th><strong>A</strong>    Using a squash court without booking it first.</th><th></th></tr></thead><tbody><tr><td><strong>B</strong>    Using the squash courts for other activities.</td><td></td></tr><tr><td><strong>C</strong>    Wearing inappropriate shoes when playing squash.</td><td></td></tr></tbody></table><p>14 Which statement is true of the swimming pool?</p><table><thead><tr><th><strong>A</strong>    Swimming times can be found on the noticeboard.</th><th></th></tr></thead><tbody><tr><td><strong>B</strong>    A picture of it is in the newsletter.</td><td></td></tr><tr><td><strong>C</strong>    It is not yet open to the public.</td><td></td></tr></tbody></table>",
